<li id="cite_note-82"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Hanukkah#cite_ref-82">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFPosner2014" class="citation news">Posner, Menachem (1 December 2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.chabad.org/news/article_cdo/aid/2778619/jewish/40-Years-Later-How-the-Chanukah-Menorah-Made-Its-Way-to-the-Public-Sphere.htm">"40 Years Later: How the Chanukah Menorah Made Its Way to the Public Sphere"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">6 October</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=40+Years+Later%3A+How+the+Chanukah+Menorah+Made+Its+Way+to+the+Public+Sphere&amp;rft.date=2014-12-01&amp;rft.aulast=Posner&amp;rft.aufirst=Menachem&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chabad.org%2Fnews%2Farticle_cdo%2Faid%2F2778619%2Fjewish%2F40-Years-Later-How-the-Chanukah-Menorah-Made-Its-Way-to-the-Public-Sphere.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHanukkah" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
